node.text:
I want you to fast-forward to you at 80 years old. Look at your hands, see the wrinkles etched in your waxy skin. Now, as that 80 year old I want you to look back at your life with two scenarios.

1. You played it safe. You worked the corporate job, and most nights when you got home you drank a bottle of wine to forget about it. You settled for the comfortable relationship, put on a bit too much weight, and started having sex less and less. You watched a lot of Netflix, were often afraid of getting sick, but all in all you did alright for yourself. 

2. You went for it. A full send to life. You quit your corporate job to follow your passion and contribute your gifts to the world. Your life was filled with adventure and mystery. You failed often, but your triumphs were glorious. You were friends with rogues, scoundrels, saints and geniuses. You trained yourself to overcome your fears, and lived a life of freedom and sovereignty. 

If you prefer scenario 2, then I wrote Go For Your Win for you. Because I prefer scenario 2 and I wrote Go For Your Win for my own younger self. It's every piece of advice I have to offer, updated and revised for this latest course release. 

Click the link in bio or head to AubreyMarcus.com/GoForYourWin to learn more

#gfyw #goforyourwin #personaldevelopment #challengeaccepted

node.text:
In order to stretch our capacities and grow as humans, we are required to do things we haven’t yet done.

Imposter syndrome is something we all feel when we’re pushing these boundaries and treading into not-yet-known territory. Everyone feels this same thing. When you realize this, you won’t have any reason left to stop yourself. 

#impostersyndrome #personalgrowth #trusttheprocess

node.text:
Our mind is a computer that is overworked, overheated, with too many tabs open, software waiting to download, and the cooling fan just can't keep up. Touching infinity is like hitting the reset button. Where for one moment the mind collapses into GOD. And that moment is timeless, and eternal. It is everything that ever was, and ever could be. Then when you reboot the computer, everything runs much more smoothly.

There are a lot of ways to touch infinity. Breathwork, plant medicine, ecstatic dance, floatation tanks, can all get you there. It doesn't matter how, it just matters that you find your own way 🤎. 

#resetyourmind #overthinking #biohacking

node.text:
I want you to fast-forward to you at 80 years old. Look at your hands, see the wrinkles etched in your waxy skin. Now, as that 80 year old I want you to look back at your life with two scenarios.

1. You played it safe. You worked the corporate job, and most nights when you got home you drank a bottle of wine to forget about it. You settled for the comfortable relationship, put on a bit too much weight, and started having sex less and less. You watched a lot of Netflix, were often afraid of getting sick, but all in all you did alright for yourself. 

2. You went for it. A full send to life. You quit your corporate job to follow your passion and contribute your gifts to the world. Your life was filled with adventure and mystery. You failed often, but your triumphs were glorious. You were friends with rogues, scoundrels, saints and geniuses. You trained yourself to overcome your fears, and lived a life of freedom and sovereignty. 

If you prefer scenario 2, then I wrote Go For Your Win for you. Because I prefer scenario 2 and I wrote Go For Your Win for my own younger self. It's every piece of advice I have to offer, updated and revised for this latest course release. 

Click the link in bio or head to AubreyMarcus.com/GoForYourWin to learn more

#gfyw #goforyourwin #personaldevelopment #challengeaccepted

First time back on the hardwood in a decade 🤩. Basketball was one of the most meaningful things in my life for a good 20 years. It was great to hear the shoes squeak and the whistles blow in the gym again.

And I had fans! Of course it was just my wife @vylanamarcus and my framily @sorayayd and @ev.thecreator but it was epic.

node.text:
I wake up with an anxiousness in my chest. Am I doing enough? Am I serving the world in the best way that I can?

Sometimes I fall into hopelessness. A depression rolls in like a fog. “I’ll never be able to do enough. People will continue to cheer the violations of our divinity and hurl abuses at their neighbors, as long as they can feel like they are better than someone else.” 

But I know, I know, I know that I am not alone. And I’ve never felt that more deeply than after this past week @soltarahealingcenter. The whole cosmos of allies seen and unseen are conspiring to help us.

Ayahuasca, the great mother, is reaching with her vine to heal the hearts and minds of her people.

A real life Dragon, Maestro Orlando, is singing his magic into the world.

My Queen @vylanamarcus and my sisters and brothers like @mehcadbrooks are with me to the end.

My @fit.for.service tribe is strong and full of heart, as are so many of you.

This is the fight we have known was coming. And we’re here for it. Hoka!

For more on my experience with Maestro Orlando check out my latest podcast with @duncantrussell and to reach out to “El Dragon” head to MaestroOrlando.com 🐉

📸 @maxwmccoy

In fact we always want the things that we aren't willing to pay the price to attain. We want to just want, not get. Because the price isn't money. The things we really want require genuine sacrifice.'.

node.text:
We want great health, but are we willing to eat clean, train hard, and sleep long?

We want to make a difference, but are we willing to sacrifice partying, leisure, and our favorite distractions to do it?

We want unconditional love.  But are we willing to give unconditional love, to ourselves and others?

Everything has a price. It’s just a matter of what we are willing to pay ❤️

#sacrifice #goals #goforyourwin

node.text:
You have to ask yourself then, are you a candle or a lump of wax? Are you going to borrow the light from others to illuminate your path, or are you going to put flame to thread and cast your own light to dispel the shadows of your soul and offer a beacon for the world? You have this singular choice: To be a warrior of the light, or to be ordinary.

Artist: @kushfineart 

#bethelight #lightwarriors #shineyourlight
